text:
The worst sliced fish I ever had in Singapore.
We ordered Double Fish Thin Bee Hoon with milk and Fresh Fish Thick Bee Hoon without milk.
1) The cook was looking around for 3 mins before telling us he does not know where the thin bee hoon is. We changed the order to noodles instead.
2) The portion given to us looks little. We gave our feedback to the aunty, only to be told it was instructions from their boss.
3) They forgotten to add milk even after repeated for 3 times. It was only added after it was served in the bowl.
Will never patronize this stall again.
Love it and the people here are so nice. Donâ€™t listen to the haters, this place is great. Be prepared to bat off flies tho, this is a hawker centre.
They moved to West Coast Hawker. Its a very normal fish soup. Nothing to shout or complain about.
Made the wrong order and insisted that its the correct order. Taste totally different and doesn't want to admit.

batang fish very fresh and big slices, prawns are de-shelled (thank goodness!!!) .  opt to add on bittergourd slices , minced pork and baby abalone! Soup is flavourful with punch of unami.  will be back again!
